                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 419.11 D 29/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your No. 240, of the 1st instant, I
                    desire to say that the Department is glad to learn of the apparently sincere
                    determination of the present administration of Panama to identify and punish
                    those responsible for the killing and wounding of American citizens in Panama on
                    July 4 last, and trusts that the investigation which has been undertaken will
                    lead to prompt results along this line.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
